# handle student numbers' data 
import csv
import os

def StudentNumber(p):
    sum = 0
    for i in range(4,20):
        sum += int(p[i])
    return sum

def degreeEnglish(p):
    if p == "M ":
        return "Master"
    elif p == "B ":
        return "4 Bachelor"	
    elif p =="C ":
        return "2 Bachelor"	
    elif p =="D ":
        return "Doctor"	
    elif p =="C ":
        return "2 Bachelor"	
    elif p == "B ": 
        return "Bachelor"
    elif p == "2 ":
        return "2 Associate"
    elif p == "5 ":
        return "5 Associate"
    else:
        return "others"

path = './data/'
save_path = './handle_data/'

fileName = input(":")
fileName_read = os.path.join(path,fileName)
reader = open(fileName_read,"r",encoding='utf-8')
fileName_write = os.path.join(save_path,fileName)
write = open(fileName_write,'w',newline='',encoding='utf-8')

reader.readline()

csv_header = ['','','','','','']

rows = csv.reader(reader)
writer = csv.writer(write)
writer.writerow(csv_header)
write_data = []

for row in rows:
    data =[]
    for i in range(0,3):
        data.append(row[i])
    data.append(degreeEnglish(row[3]))
    data.append(StudentNumber(row))
    data.append(row[20])
    write_data.append(data)

for i in write_data:
    writer.writerow(i)

reader.close()
write.close()

# Read dataset
def read_dataset(filename):
    
    filename_read = os.path.join(path,filename)
    return sc.textFile(filename_read)

# remover header
def removeHeader(dataset):
    header = dataset.first()
    remove_header = dataset.filter(lambda x : x != header)
    return remove_header

sqlContext = SQLContext(sc)
#creat students' table
def CreatStudentTable(dataset):
    dataset =  dataset.map(lambda p:
                       Row(
                           Unumber = int(p[0]),
                           Name = str(p[1]),
                           StudyClassification = str(p[2]),
                           Degree = str(p[3]),
                           studentNumber = int(p[4]),
                           City = str(p[5])
                       ))
    return dataset

def CreatRegisteredTable(dataset):
    dataset = dataset.map(lambda p:
                        Row(
                            System = str(p[0]),
                            SchoolClass = str(p[1]),
                            Name = str(p[2]),
                            StudyClassification = str(p[3]),
                            Degree = str(p[4]),
                            Rate = float(p[5])
                            ))
    return dataset

def studentNumberPercent(name,title):
    count = []
    Less_3000 = studentNumbers[studentNumbers[name]<=3000].count()
    Less_6000 = studentNumbers[(studentNumbers[name]<=6000) & (studentNumbers[name] > 3000)].count()
    Less_9000 = studentNumbers[(studentNumbers[name]<=9000) & (studentNumbers[name] > 6000)].count()
    Less_12000 = studentNumbers[(studentNumbers[name]<=12000) & (studentNumbers[name] > 9000)].count()
    More_12001 = studentNumbers[(studentNumbers[name]> 12000)].count()
    count.append(Less_3000['Name'])
    count.append(Less_6000['Name'])
    count.append(Less_9000['Name'])
    count.append(Less_12000['Name'])
    count.append(More_12001['Name'])
    drawPie(count,title)

def drawPie(count,title):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    labels = '3000','6000','9000','12000','12001'
    colors = ['yellowgreen', 'gold', 'lightskyblue', 'lightcoral','red']
    explode = (0, 0.1, 0, 0)

    ax.pie(count,  labels=labels, colors=colors,autopct='%1.1f%%', shadow=True, startangle=90,radius=1.2)

    ax.set(aspect="equal", title=title)#
    
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_path,title+'.png'))

    plt.show()

def less_than_3000(student,registered):
    Numbers = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT Unumber,Name,sum(studentNumber) Numbers,City
                                FROM {}
                                GROUP BY Unumber, Name, City""".format(student))
    school = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT distinct Name,System, SchoolClass
                                FROM {}""".format(registered))
    Semester = Numbers.join(school,Numbers.Name == school.Name,"leftouter")
    Less_than = Semester.filter((Semester["Numbers"]<=3000))
    Image = Less_than.select('SchoolClass').groupBy('SchoolClass').count()
    Image_pandas = Image.toPandas()
    return Image_pandas

def less_than_3000_city(student,title,saveName):
    Numbers = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT Unumber,Name,sum(studentNumber) Numbers,City
                                FROM {}
                                GROUP BY Unumber, Name, City""".format(student))
    Less_than = Numbers.filter((Numbers["Numbers"]<=3000))
    Image = Less_than.select('City').groupBy('City').count()
    Image_pandas = Image.toPandas().set_index("City")
    Image_pandas.T
    Image_pandas['count'].plot(kind='bar', title=title,figsize=(18,9))
    plt.savefig(os.path.join(save_path,saveName))
    plt.show()
    return Image_pandas.T

In [108]:
def SystemClassification(student,registered):
    Numbers = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT Unumber,Name,sum(studentNumber) Numbers,City
                                FROM {}
                                GROUP BY Unumber, Name, City""".format(student))
    school = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT distinct Name,System, SchoolClass
                                FROM {}""".format(registered))
    Semester = Numbers.join(school,Numbers.Name == school.Name,"leftouter")
    Less_than = Semester.filter((Semester["Numbers"]<=3000)&(Semester['SchoolClass'] == ''))
    Image = Less_than.select('System').groupBy('System').count()
    Image_pandas = Image.toPandas()
    return Image_pandas

def pltDegreeRate(table):
    Rate = sqlContext.sql("""SELECT Name,Degree,Rate ,SchoolClass,System
                             FROM {}
                             WHERE Rate < 60 and StudyClassification ='D '""".format(table))
    
    return Rate
